notesStmt.note: Title from leaf pasted onto front endleaf verso.

msContents.summary: Genealogies of noble families of Venice, with small engraved coats of arms pasted in throughout, some have become detached, some coats of arms are illustrated in pen-and-ink. Arranged alphabetically with index at the end.

msItem.title: Libro d'oro ossia delle famiglie nobili venete
msItem.author: Coronelli, Vincenzo, 1650-1718

supportDesc.extent: 167 leaves plus 17 leaves tipped in : 278 x 198 mm. bound to 283 x 207 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (contemporary paper) + 167 + i (contemporary paper) leaves; 1-321, [xiii]; contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners. 17 folios tipped in (some detached).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illustrated with pasted-in engraved coats of arms, and some drawn in pen-and-ink.
